---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import SearchDemo from '../components/SearchDemo'
---

<Layout title="FlexSearch Demo">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">FlexSearch Demo</h1>

    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
      <p class="text-lg text-center mb-6">
        This is a demo of the FlexSearch implementation, a fast and
        privacy-focused client-side search solution.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200 mb-2">
          Privacy First
        </h2>
        <p class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300">
          Unlike traditional search solutions, FlexSearch runs entirely in your
          browser. No search queries are sent to any server, preserving your
          privacy while still providing fast and relevant search results.
        </p>
      </div>

      <SearchDemo client:load />
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How It Works</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The search index is pre-built during site compilation and loaded as a
        JavaScript file. All search operations run in your browser using
        FlexSearch's optimized algorithms.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-8">
        This provides both excellent performance and complete privacy, as your
        search queries never leave your device.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-left">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Fast Performance</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            FlexSearch is one of the fastest full-text search libraries
            available, outperforming alternatives even with large datasets.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Fuzzy Search</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Handles typos and partial matches, making it easy for users to find
            what they're looking for even with imperfect queries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Lightweight</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Adds minimal overhead to your site with a tiny footprint of around
            5KB, ensuring fast page loads.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
